Status Lifecycle

Each execution plan follows a defined lifecycle.

Status	Description
Draft	Recommendation created
Validated	Policy checks completed
Simulated	Execution successfully simulated
Pending Approval	Awaiting governance approval
Approved	Authorized for execution
Executing	Transaction submitted
Completed	Successfully confirmed
Failed	Execution unsuccessful
Cancelled	Execution intentionally aborted
Security Principles

The Execution Layer enforces strict operational controls.

Key principles:

No automatic fund movement by default
Human approval required
Multisig-first architecture
Policy validation before execution
Read-only simulation before signing
Complete audit trail
Separation of analysis and execution
Immutable execution history
Example Workflow

A treasury exceeds its ETH allocation target.

The Portfolio Manager recommends reducing ETH exposure.
The Risk Engine confirms the action complies with treasury policy.
The Execution Layer simulates an ETH → USDC swap.
Gas costs and slippage are estimated.
A transaction plan is generated.
Treasury managers review the proposal.
The multisig wallet approves the transaction.
The transaction is executed and monitored until confirmation.
